# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Local `go build .` output at module root (no extension on Unix).
/locutus

# Claude Code per-machine state — settings.json accumulates absolute paths
# from Bash/Read allow entries that are specific to whoever ran the session,
# so we keep it local rather than shared. .claude/plans/ IS tracked (it's
# the implementation-plan source of truth per CLAUDE.md).
/.claude/settings.json
/.claude/settings.local.json

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Locutus runtime — transient dispatch coordination records (DJ-073).
# Durable reconciliation state under .locutus/state/ IS git-tracked per DJ-068;
# only in-flight workstreams are excluded. A record exists while an adopt run
# is mid-dispatch and is deleted on terminal transition or drift-invalidation.
/.locutus/workstreams/

# Agent memory (DJ-077). Learned context curated by one agent for future
# agents; transient, not audit material. A fresh clone starts with an empty
# memory and agents rebuild from project state as needed.
/.locutus/memory/

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/
